Uses of Package
org.biohipi.image

  • Packages that use org.biohipi.image 
    Package Description
    org.biohipi.examples
    Useful examples for understanding the use of BioHIPI.
    org.biohipi.image
    A group of classes for representing and manipulating images.
    org.biohipi.image.io
    A group of classes for reading (decoding) and writing (encoding) images in various storage formats such as JPEG, PNG, NIFTI, DICOM.
    org.biohipi.imagebundle
    Classes for storing and manipulating collections of images.
    org.biohipi.imagebundle.mapreduce
    Classes for processing BioHIBs including producing input splits and reading and decoding image records in the context of a MapReduce program.
    org.biohipi.tools
    Several useful programs to perform analysis operations and basic operations such as import and export of images from BioHipiImageBundle.
  • Classes in org.biohipi.image used by org.biohipi.examples 
    Class and Description
    BioHipiImage
    An abstract base class from which all concrete image classes in BioHIPI must be derived.
    BioHipiImageHeader
    The header information for a BioHipiImage.
    DicomImage
    A DICOM image represented as an dataset of Java Objects.
    NiftiImage
    A NIfTI image represented as an 4-dimensional array of Java doubles.
    RasterImage
    A raster image represented as an array of Java floats, which represents a flat array of uncompressed image pixel data stored in interleaved raster-scan order (e.g., RGBRGBRGB...).
  • Classes in org.biohipi.image used by org.biohipi.image 
    Class and Description
    BioHipiImage
    An abstract base class from which all concrete image classes in BioHIPI must be derived.
    BioHipiImage.BioHipiImageType
    Enumeration of the supported image object types in BioHIPI (FloatImage, ByteImage, NiftiImage, DicomImage).
    BioHipiImageHeader
    The header information for a BioHipiImage.
    BioHipiImageHeader.BioHipiColorSpace
    Enumeration of the color spaces supported in BioHIPI.
    BioHipiImageHeader.BioHipiImageFormat
    Enumeration of the image storage formats supported in BioHIPI (JPEG, PNG, NIFTI, DICOM).
    RasterImage
    A raster image represented as an array of Java floats, which represents a flat array of uncompressed image pixel data stored in interleaved raster-scan order (e.g., RGBRGBRGB...).
